quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  71,1,"We sent Noah to his people: \"Warn your people before some painful torment comes to them"
  71,2,"He said: \"My folk, I am a plain warner for you"
  71,3,"serve God and heed Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive some of your offences for you and postpone things for you until a specific deadline. God´s deadline will never be postponed once it comes, if you only realized it"
  71,5,"He said: \"My Lord, I have appealed to my people night and day"
  71,6,and my appeal has only made them flee farther away from me
  71,7,"Each time I appeal to them to ask You to forgive them, they stick their fingers in their ears and try to wrap themselves up in their clothing. They persist in that and have become so overbearing"
  71,8,Next I appealed to them publicly
  71,9,then I broadcast it to them and confided with them privately
  71,10,"and said: ´Seek forgiveness from your Lord; He has been so Forgiving"
  71,11,He causes the sky to send torrents down upon you
  71,12,"and He supplies you with wealth and children, and grants you gardens and even grants you rivers"
  71,13,´What is wrong that you do not expect God to have any dignity
  71,14,while He has created you over and over again
  71,15,Have you not (all) considered how God created seven matching Heavens
  71,16,"He has set the moon as a light among them, and set the sun up as a source of light"
  71,17,God makes you grow out of the earth like plants
  71,18,"Later He will return you to it, and bring you forth once more"
  71,19,´God has laid the earth out as a carpet for you
  71,20,so you may travel around on highways which lead through mountain passes.´